#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"Flux Studio is a soon-to-be developed <0>Digital Audio Workstation</0> using <1>Rust</1>. My goal is to develop a first-class DAW for playing and learning\n"
"music. My goals are ambitious, but I will do my best to see this project through. As you may have guessed, music is\n"
"my passion, and I want it to be a central element of my life, whether through playing music or developing this\n"
"software."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"This is also an opportunity for me to learn Rust, which seems like a really promising programming language. You can\n"
"find out more at <0>their website</0> directly for more details, but it might\n"
"just become my go-to language for almost every use cases. Despite the fact that the Rust community is relatively new,\n"
"the Rustaceans (the name of the Rust developers' community) are very active, and the available resources are constantly\n"
"growing. There is even debate about whether this language should be included in the Linux Kernel. I will leave you to\n"
"do your own research on this subject, as this is not the main topic of this page."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid "The content of this page is bound to change as the project progresses."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid "Main goals"
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"My first goal is to successfully process and generate live audio signals. I want to be able to manipulate the gain\n"
"and recognise or decompose the frequencies within the signal. The next step would be to add a graphical user\n"
"interface (GUI) for manipulating the signals. I think the GUI will be the most challenging aspect of this project.\n"
"As you may have gathered from this website, UI/UX design is not my forte. However, I don't plan on creating a\n"
"substandard GUI, even if it takes me a long time to refine it. I am still thinking about the next steps in this\n"
"project. I have lots of ideas, but I don't yet know the intermediate steps, and I need to be realistic about which\n"
"features I can actually implement."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid "Expected difficulties"
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"As I have never used Rust before, it is difficult for me to anticipate the issues I will encounter on this\n"
"project. However, I think the main issues will stem from the relatively new Rust ecosystem, since many of its\n"
"crates are not yet mature. For example, there is no consensus on which crate to use for creating graphical\n"
"interfaces for applications. Many different projects are being developed to meet the needs of the community, each\n"
"with their own particular features, but none of them are particularly notable. I need to do a lot of research for\n"
"this, and I will probably publish an article about my findings."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"The second obstacle that I fear the most is developing a cross-platform application. From the outset, I intend to\n"
"develop Flux Studio with modular code to simplify the management of the various crates required for each operating\n"
"system. However, I am still anxious about the moment when I attempt to optimise the application. I have no\n"
"experience of cross-platform development so far, so my worries may be unfounded."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/flux-studio/+page.svelte
#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid "Roadmap"
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"This website is my way of justifying taking a year off from university. If you're not sure what I mean, you can find\n"
"out more on <0>this page</0>. It is also a way for me to keep track of my\n"
"activities, projects, and associated goals. I think it could be useful for business partners or recruiters who want\n"
"to find out more about a candidate before making an offer. If you are interested in this, I am definitely the person\n"
"for the job - don't hesitate to contact me! More seriously, I will develop this website in my free time to promote\n"
"myself and my projects."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid "Svelte and SvelteKit"
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"I was curious about learning how to use a web development framework, so this is also the perfect opportunity to\n"
"make something with the ones I had in mind: Svelte and SvelteKit. I've heard a lot of good things about them, so I\n"
"thought I'd give them a try, and I have to say, I was impressed. Even though I didn't have much experience with\n"
"Javascript or HTML/CSS, they made it really easy to build something decent. I'll probably write an article about\n"
"it later, when I'm a bit more experienced and confident in explaining things, but I encourage you to check <0>their website</0> for more details."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid "Main Milestones"
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/[[locale]]/projects/website/+page.svelte
msgid ""
"My first goal is to create a fully functional application comprising all its pages, error handling and efficient\n"
"back-end logic. Then, I will try to make the entire application responsive. Finally, I will add quality-of-life\n"
"features such as multiple language support and a more efficient UI. Once all of this has been achieved, I will\n"
"update the style periodically (perhaps with seasonal themes) and add content in the form of articles and projects.\n"
"I envision the articles feature as interactive: the main point is to share my knowledge and experiences and\n"
"showcase my hobbies, but most importantly, to learn from your feedback and constantly improve."
msgstr ""

